
Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad Friday called upon the people to save water at a time when the water shortage problem has affected various states including the capital city of Kuala Lumpur. A severe water shortage has hit the northern province of Tak in Thailand as reservoirs have dried up, a report available here Monday said. More than 170,000 children under one year of age die every year because of the shortage of potable water in Afghanistan, according to a press report reaching here on Wednesday. The Addis Ababa Regional Water and Sewerage Authority announced that the shortage of potable water in the capital city of Ethiopia will be solved in the last quarter of this year. Water shortage in the Pakistani capital of Islamabad is expected to deteriorate as water reservoir can meet demand of the consumers just for 12 days. A Lebanese official has warned that his country is suffering an annual water shortage of more than 1 billion cubic meters, the Daily Star reported Friday. Drought in Vietnam has caused a serious water shortage affecting about 3 million people in the recent months, Vietnam's English newspaper The Saigon Times Daily reported Thursday. Tanzanian Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye has urged residents in capital Dar es Salaam to use water sparingly as another water shortage is imminent. A project will be launched this year to solve the water shortage problem for Yan'an, an old revolutionary base in northwest China's Shaanxi Province.

